<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPENING OF LIBRARY-MUSEUM RETURNS NIXON TO LIMELIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Worse than burning the flag -- worse than parading Willie Horton -- worse than 
the Iran-Contra guilt. 
</P>
<P>
Worse than all these is the desecration of all the ideals our country is 
supposed to stand for was the obscene spectacle of three ex-Presidents honoring 
a man who escaped impeachment by resigning. 
</P>
<P>
At this celebration, where were all the former jailbirds from his 
co-conspirators who were found guilty of crimes lesser than his? 
</P>
<P>
What greater shame can our ex-presidents Bush, Reagan and Ford bring upon 
American history? This was a day that exceeds all in infamy. 
</P>
<P>
GLENN L. ANDERSON 
</P>
<P>
Topanga 
</P>
