<P>
Lee and Scorsese Do the Right Thing: Film directors Martin Scorsese and Spike 
Lee have teamed up on a new government advertising campaign that sends 
teen-agers the message: Drug use can lead to unsafe sexual behavior and AIDS. 
The television ads were directed by Scorsese and narrated by Lee. 
</P>
<P>
The television, radio and print campaign focuses on people ages 12-16, a 
segment of the population who are "using alcohol and illicit drugs and often 
engage in sexual activity while under the influence of these substances," said 
Charles Schuster, director of the National Institute on Drug Abuse, the agency 
sponsoring the $3-million public service campaign. The message found in the 
ads' tag line: "AIDS. Another way drugs can kill." BETH KLEID 
