<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Teen-Ager in Love? Doo-wop singer Dion is challenging a request that he 
undergo blood testing in a paternity suit filed by an air conditioner repairman 
claiming to be his son from a youthful romance, an attorney in West Palm Beach, 
Fla., said Thursday. Palm Beach County Judge John Phillips heard the request 
Wednesday and was expected to rule by today. 
</P>
<P>
Dion Ambrogio, 33, said his mother, Gail Schweitzer, told him when he turned 18 
that he was the son of singer Dion Dimucci. Dimucci, who uses only his first 
name Dion, had a string of hits in the late 1950s with Dion and the Belmonts, 
including "A Teen-ager in Love" and "Where or When." The singer, who is 
married, lives in Boca Raton. BETH KLEID 
</P>
