<HEADLINE>
<P>
PORT HUENEME; 
</P>
<P>
MAN CHARGED WITH ASSAULT, KIDNAPING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Port Hueneme man was charged Thursday with five felonies in connection with 
the kidnaping and sexual assault of his housemate and her 7-year-old daughter, 
Dist. Atty. Michael D. Bradbury announced. 
</P>
<P>
Bradbury's office filed a criminal complaint against Justo Dungca, 34, charging 
him with kidnaping, child molestation and attempted murder of the child, and 
kidnaping and sexual battery of the mother in connection with last week's 
alleged abduction. 
</P>
<P>
The district attorney's office was expected to serve a warrant on Dungca on 
Thursday in Las Vegas, where he has been held without bail in the Clark County 
Detention Center since his arrest July 20, Deputy Dist. Atty. Vincent J. 
O'Neill Jr. said. 
</P>
<P>
On July 19, authorities said, Dungca bound and gagged the girl and her mother 
and held them captive in his bedroom in Port Hueneme, where authorities said he 
sexually assaulted the woman. 
</P>
<P>
Dungca then forced the two into the woman's car and drove to Anaheim, where the 
woman managed to escape, authorities said. Dungca was found in Las Vegas the 
next morning as he tried to sell the car. 
</P>
<P>
As Las Vegas police closed in, Dungca grabbed the girl in a stranglehold and 
banged her head against the floor before officers could rescue her, said Lt. 
Greg Jolley, Las Vegas police spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
If convicted of all counts, Dungca faces a maximum sentence of 28 years in 
prison, O'Neill said. MACK REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
