<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARIE SCHARPER; RETIRED PUBLICIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marie Scharper, a Hollywood publicist who represented such stars as Bette Davis 
and Joan Crawford, has died in Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
She was 86. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Scharper worked at Warner Bros. from the 1930s to the 1950s as a publicist 
for several actors and actresses, including Davis, Crawford and Ann Sheridan. 
</P>
<P>
She was also a personal publicist to several other performers, including Lorne 
Green, said her executor, Jay Eller. 
</P>
<P>
She retired in the late 1960s. 
</P>
<P>
She died Sunday of natural causes at the Motion Picture and Television Hospital 
in Woodland Hills, Eller said. 
</P>
<P>
She had lived at the Motion Picture and Television Country Home for five years. 
</P>
<P>
She was born Marie Dyches on March 30, 1904, in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
In 1937, she joined the Publicists Guild as a charter member. In 1975, she 
married William Albert (Al) Scharper, former managing editor of Daily Variety, 
who died in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Scharper is survived by a great-nephew, Jeffrey Sturmthal, and a 
great-niece, Robin Sturmthal of Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
No services are scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce Brothers Cunningham &amp; O'Connor Mortuary in Los Angeles is handling 
the arrangements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
