<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two security guards at a San Ysidro trailer park were arrested after they posed 
as immigration officers and robbed three illegal immigrants, San Diego police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The three immigrants were taken to the security office of the Border Village 
Trailer Park in the 1100 block of San Ysidro Boulevard shortly after midnight 
Thursday and robbed of $115, police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Carter, 23, of National City and Tommy Corley, 20, of San Diego were 
arrested by police on suspicion of kidnaping, robbery and unlawful arrest and 
were held at County Jail after being identified by the three men, Robinson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The undocumented migrants, all from Colima, Mexico, had crossed the border on 
foot and were stopped by the security guards as they were walking through the 
trailer park, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson said that, once the men were released, they called police who made the 
arrests about 1 a.m. Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
