<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FILING OPENS FOR HOSPITAL BOARD SEATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Filing has opened for candidates for two seats on the five-member board of the 
South Bay Hospital District, a foundation that provides money for public health 
programs in Manhattan Beach, Hermosa Beach and Redondo Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Seats held by Ken Johnson and Jean G. McMillan will be contested. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who was appointed to the board last August, said he will run for a 
four-year term. McMillan, a board member for 10 years, was out of town and 
could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
Candidacy forms may be obtained from the Los Angeles County Registrar-Recorder, 
5557 Ferguson Drive, Commerce, between 8 a.m. and 5 p.m. Candidates must file 
by 5 p.m. Aug. 10. Candidates must be registered voters and reside in one of 
the three beach cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
