<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: INTERIM SCHOOL SUPERINTENDENT CHOSEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Retired school administrator and longtime El Segundo resident Walther Puffer 
has been named interim superintendent of the El Segundo Unified School 
District. 
</P>
<P>
Puffer, 61, begins work Monday, replacing Supt. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Bertain, who will become associate director of ACTION, a federal agency 
that coordinates such national volunteer programs as VISTA and the Retired 
Senior Volunteer Program. 
</P>
<P>
Puffer retired a year ago after 35 years with the Beverly Hills Unified School 
District, where he was assistant superintendent. He has lived in El Segundo 
since 1941 and attended school there. 
</P>
<P>
Puffer will serve El Segundo on a part-time basis until Bertain's successor is 
chosen, probably in two to three months. He will receive between $4,000 and 
$6,000 a month, depending on the amount of time he works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
