<TEXT>
<P>
Federal prosecutors said in New York City that they have closed an eight-month 
investigation into Mayor David N. Dinkins' sale of cable stock to his son and 
will not file criminal charges. In a brief statement, prosecutor Andrew 
Manloney said the investigation "has been completed without the filing of 
criminal charges." Questions centered on whether Dinkins gave 588 shares of 
Inner City Broadcasting Corp. stock to his son, David Jr., through a genuine 
transaction, how much it was actually worth and whether taxes were fully paid 
on the deal. 
