<TEXT>
<P>
Don G. McNeill's Clever Trevor, eligible for the $600,000 Arlington Challenge 
Cup at Arlington International Racecourse on Aug. 4, has suffered a bone chip 
in a knee and will be sidelined until spring. 
</P>
<P>
The 4-year-old gelded son of Slewacide, owned and bred by his owner in 
Oklahoma, has won 12 of 20 starts and has earned $1,072,083. He won his first 
two races this year, allowance events at Arlington, and then finished fourth to 
Beau Genius in the $300,000 Michigan Mile and One Eighth. 
