</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ceiling Fan Recall: Builders Square is recalling 10,000 ceiling fans because of 
a defect that can cause the blades to separate from the motor while the fan is 
in use, said the Consumer Product Safety Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The voluntary recall involves eight models of 52-inch Bay Breeze ceiling fans 
distributed by Builders Square Inc. of San Antonio, Tex. The fans, sold with 
and without lights, were distributed nationwide from October, 1989, until two 
months ago. Consumers should stop using the fans and return them to any 
Builders Square store for a refund or call the company at (800) 634-5949. 
</P>
