<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Yields Fall: Yields for 52-week T-bills fell to 7.34% at the monthly 
auction, the lowest since 7.21% on Jan. 11, the Treasury Department said. The 
government said it sold about $10.5 billion worth of the bills and that the 
average investment rate was 7.88% at a price of $9,257.80 per $10,000 face 
value. At the last auction June 28, the bills yielded 7.52%. 
</P>
