<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DOCTOR CHARGED IN RAPES FACES 3 NEW COUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A West Los Angeles orthopedic surgeon recently charged with raping three female 
patients was charged Thursday with three counts of sexual battery against two 
other women, authorities said. The new misdemeanor charges against Dr. Yahya 
Lavi, 52, were filed in Los Angeles Municipal Court, according to Deputy Dist. 
Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Lydia Bodin. Lavi remains free on $500,000 bail after his arrest July 12 on 
charges of raping and sexually assaulting the three patients. 
</P>
<P>
In all, Lavi faces two felony counts each of rape by use of drugs, sexual 
battery and penetration by a foreign object; three counts of forcible rape, and 
one count of forcible oral copulation. He also faces five misdemeanor sexual 
battery counts. A hearing on the matter, postponed Thursday, was rescheduled 
for Sept. 12. 
</P>
