<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BOY HIT BY CAR IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 10-year-old Santa Ana boy was listed in critical condition Thursday suffering 
from injuries received when he darted into the path of an car and was hit, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Bernardo Rodriguez was taken by paramedics to Western Medical Center in Santa 
Ana on Wednesday night after being struck by a vehicle as he attempted to cross 
in the 900 block of South Harbor Boulevard at about 9:05 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's injuries included trauma to the head, a pelvic fracture and a broken 
left leg, according to a hospital spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the driver of the car, who was not cited, apparently did not see 
the boy, who was crossing in the middle of the street and not at a crosswalk. 
</P>
<P>
Although the incident is still under investigation, police spokeswoman Maureen 
Thomas said it does not appear that drugs or alcohol were involved. 
</P>
