<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
FRENCH RELEASE IRANIAN ASSASSIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anis Naccache, convicted of killing two people during a botched assassination 
attempt ordered by Iran, was freed by the French government today after 
spending 10 years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
The Justice Ministry said Naccache and four accomplices left France for Iran 
this afternoon after their release was ordered by President Francois 
Mitterrand. 
</P>
<P>
Naccache, whose release had been sought by several hard-line Arab leaders, went 
on a 19-week hunger strike ending in January in a bid to obtain his release. 
</P>
<P>
He and three members of his group were sentenced to life imprisonment for an 
attempt in 1980 to kill Shahpour Bakhtiar, Iran's prime minister before the 
1979 Islamic revolution. A fifth member of the team received a 20-year 
sentence. Bakhtiar escaped injury and still lives in Paris, but a policeman and 
a bystander were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Anis Naccache 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
