<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
PRANK IMPERILS 2 FIREFIGHTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LEEDS, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two British firefighters had to be rescued from a sewer today after trudging 
through water in search of children imitating the cartoon capers of the Teenage 
Mutant Ninja Turtles. 
</P>
<P>
The youngsters were already above ground by the time their exhausted would-be 
rescuers, carrying heavy resuscitation equipment, radioed a colleague to come 
and get them. 
</P>
<P>
"It may be a craze but these children need a good spanking," said a fire 
brigade spokesman in this northern city. "It's a dangerous game and it nearly 
cost the lives of three firemen." 
</P>
<P>
The sewer-dwelling turtles have an avid following among children in Britain 
where they are known as Heroes rather than Ninja turtles in the interests of 
nonviolence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
