<TEXT>
<P>
An Alabama newspaper reported today that Arkansas and Florida State have 
accepted invitations to join the Southeastern Conference. 
</P>
<P>
The Alabama Journal quoted an unnamed source, identified as a "highly ranked 
SEC official," who confirmed that the two universities would join the SEC, 
bringing the number of SEC teams to 12. 
</P>
<P>
Arkansas Athletic Director Frank Broyles said today a decision for his school 
would be announced by Aug. 15. 
