<P>
3 IRAN ATHLETES ASK U.S. ASYLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AMSTERDAM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Iranian athletes taking part in the World Championships for the Disabled 
have asked asylum in the United States, the U.S. Embassy said today. 
</P>
<P>
The three were part of a 125-member Iranian delegation, and two were blind. 
</P>
<P>
Neither the names nor the whereabouts of the three were known. 
</P>
<P>
Iranian team leader Feraidoon Akhbari was quoted on Dutch television as saying 
the atmosphere among the Iranian athletes was oppressive. 
</P>
<P>
The championships included such sports as basketball, track and field, soccer, 
judo and wheelchair marathon. 
</P>
