<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGHLAND TALK PREVAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Highland Talk, ridden by John Velasquez, collared the leader entering the 
stretch and then drew away to beat Etoile Eternelle by three lengths in the 
$47,000 Lamb Chop Purse for fillies and mares 3 and up at Belmont Park on 
Thursday. Etoile Eternelle finished two lengths ahead of Gottagetitdone in the 
field of six. 
</P>
</TEXT>
